//api.github.com/repos/cirruslycurious/ai-learning-hub/labels/feature","name":"feature","color":"0075ca","default":false,"description":"New feature or enhancement"}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2026-02-16T18:14:33Z","updated_at":"2026-02-16T18:41:56Z","closed_at":"2026-02-16T18:41:56Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"OWNER","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Story 2.8: Auth Error Codes\n\n**As a** client developer,\n**I want** consistent, machine-parseable auth error responses across all auth flows,\n**so that** I can handle errors correctly (retry on rate-limit, re-auth on expired token, show invite UI when needed, etc.).\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n\n- AC1: Auth error responses use ADR-008 format: `{ error: { code, message, requestId } }`\n- AC2: Uses auth-specific error codes: EXPIRED_TOKEN, INVALID_API_KEY, REVOKED_API_KEY, SUSPENDED_ACCOUNT, SCOPE_INSUFFICIENT, INVITE_REQUIRED, INVALID_INVITE_CODE, RATE_LIMITED\n- AC3: Authorizer deny() errorCode available in context for future Gateway Response formatting\n- AC4: Scope middleware returns 403 with SCOPE_INSUFFICIENT code and scope details\n- AC5: Rate limiter returns 429 with RATE_LIMITED code and Retry-After header (verify preserved from Story 2.7)\n\n### References\n\n- Part of Epic 2: User Authentication & API Keys\n- Story file: `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/2-8-auth-error-codes.md`\n- ADR-008: Error Handling, ADR-013: Authentication Provider\n\n<!-- bmad:story=2.8 bmad:epic=Epic-2 -->","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/cirruslycurious/ai-learning-hub/issues/140/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/cirruslycurious/ai-learning-hub/issues/1